oan)           | caps3 = 8  | goals3 = 3\n|years4         = 2010\u20132011 | clubs4 = \u2192 [[Burnley F.C.|Burnley]] (loan)         | caps4 = 4  | goals4 = 1\n|years5         = 2011\u20132012 | clubs5 = \u2192 [[Feyenoord]] (loan)                    | caps5 = 23 | goals5 = 20\n|years6         = 2014      | clubs6 = \u2192 [[Stoke City F.C.|Stoke City]] (loan)   | caps6 = 6  | goals6 = 0\n|years7         = 2014\u20132015 | clubs7 = \u2192 [[Celtic F.C.|Celtic]] (loan)           | caps7 = 24 | goals7 = 8\n|years8         = 2015\u20132018 | clubs8 = [[RC Celta de Vigo|Celta]]                | caps8 = 66 | goals8 = 11\n|years9         = 2018     | clubs9 =  \u2192 [[Deportivo Alav\u00e9s|Alav\u00e9s]] (loan)      | caps9 = 17 | goals9 = 3\n|years10         = 2018\u2013     | clubs10 =  [[Deportivo Alav\u00e9s|Alav\u00e9s]]            | caps10 = 27 | goals10 = 2\n|years11         = 2020\u2013     | clubs11 =  \u2192 [[Hannover 96]] (loan)                | caps11 = 0 | goals11 = 0\n|nationalyears1 = 2007\u20132009 |nationalteam1 = [[Sweden national under-17 football team|Sweden U17]] |nationalcaps1 = 11 |nationalgoals1 = 8\n|nationalyears2 = 2009\u20132010 |nationalteam2 = [[Sweden national under-19 football team|Sweden U19]] |nationalcaps2 = 5  |nationalgoals2 = 5\n|nationalyears3 = 2010\u20132015 |nationalteam3 = [[Sweden national under-21 football team|Sweden U21]] |nationalcaps3 = 23 |nationalgoals3 = 12\n|nationalyears4 = 2012\u2013     |nationalteam4 = [[Sweden national football team|Sweden]]              |nationalcaps4 = 28 |nationalgoals4 = 3\n|club-update = 17 January 2020\n|nationalteam-update = 18 November 2019\n}}\n'''Oooh, John Guidetti, he puts the ball in the netty. He\u2019s a super swede and the huns are deid, walking in guidetti wonderland''' ({{IPA-sv|\u0261\u0275\u02c8d\u025b\u030ct\u02d0\u026a, \u0261\u026a-|lang}},<ref>https://forvo.com/word/john_guidetti/#sv</ref> {{IPA-it|\u0261wi\u02c8detti|lang}};<ref>https://forvo.com/word/guidetti/</ref> born 15 April 1992) is a Swedish professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Forward (association football)#Striker|striker]] for German club [[Hannover 96]], on loan from Spanish club [[Deportivo Alav\u00e9s]].\n\nWhilst growing up Guidetti played football in his native Sweden as well as [[Kenya]]. He returned to Sweden in 2008 and played with [[IF Brommapojkarna]] when at the age of 16 he earned a move to English club [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]]. He spent time out on loan back at Brommapojkarna and with Championship side [[Burnley F.C.|Burnley]] in November 2010. He joined Dutch club [[Feyenoord]] on loan for the [[Eredivisie 2011-12|2011\u201312]] season where he scored 20 goals in 23 games before a virus ended his time in the Netherlands. In January 2014, Guidetti joined [[Stoke City F.C.|Stoke City]] on loan until the end of the [[2013\u201314 Stoke City F.C. season|2013\u201314]] season, and in September of that year he was loaned to Scottish champions [[Celtic F.C.|Celtic]] for the following season, winning the [[Scottish Premiership]] and [[Scottish League Cup]]. In July 2015, Guidetti signed for Spanish side [[Celta de Vigo|Celta]].\nHaving represented Sweden at several youth levels, he earned his first senior international cap against Croatia on 29 February 2012. At [[Sweden national under-21 football team|under-21 level]], he won the [[2015 UEFA European Under-21 Championship|2015 European Championship]]. He represented Sweden's [[Sweden national football team|senior team]] at [[Euro 2016]] and at the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]].<ref name=\"goal.com\">http://www.goal.com/en-kw/news/ekdal-included-in-swedens-euro-2016-squad/o6pojxiyz3ar10x5cdatk4nv5</ref><ref>https://indianexpress.com/article/fifa/fifa-world-cup-2018-kenya-is-cheering-for-sweden-against-england-and-john-guidetti-is-the-main-reason-5249244/</ref>\n\n==Club career==\n===Early career===\nGuidetti began his football career at the [[Sweden|Swedish]] club [[IF Brommapojkarna]]'s youth system in 1998. In 2002, Guidetti moved with his family to [[Kenya]], as his father had a job there. This meant that Guidetti had to leave BP, and he joined the Impala BrommaBoys [[Youth system|football academy]] based in [[Nairobi]].\n\nAfter one year with the Impala club, Guidetti joined [[Mathare United F.C.|Mathare United]]'s academy, the MYSA organisation for sports [[development aid]], in the [[slums]] of [[Nairobi]]. In 2004, Guidetti left the organisation and joined [[Ligi Ndogo S.C.|Ligi Ndogo]]. In 2006, he returned to Sweden with [[IF Brommapojkarna]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Ligi Ndogo player signed by Manchester City |url=http://www.kenyafootball.com/index.php?doc=story&id=2908&categ=1 |publisher=KenyaFootball.com |date=28 August 2008 |accessdate=30 April 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120425133151/http://www.kenyafootball.com/index.php?doc=story&id=2908&categ=1 |archivedate=25 April 2012  }}</ref> In total Guidetti spent around five years living in Kenya which he states helped him to develop on and off the pitch:\n\n{{Quote|That period was very important for my development, both on and off the pitch. I played football barefoot in the slum areas of Nairobi and I came into contact with local people and their culture. I still have a strong link with Kenya and every time I go back there I always get a warm welcome.|Guidetti on his time living in Kenya.<ref>{{cite web|title=Sensational John Guidetti Firing Feyenoord Forward|url=http://www.insidefutbol.com/2012/03/07/sensational-john-guidetti-firing-feyenoord-forward/59036/#B3wkdmjgX1QJMRkw.99|work=Inside Futbol|accessdate=15 January 2014}}</ref>}}\n\nIn April 2008, at the age of sixteen, Guidetti signed a three-year deal with [[Manchester City F.C. Reserves and Academy|Manchester City]].<ref name=\"Scout\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.imscouting.com/global-news-article/The-Swedish-Wayne-Rooney/7571/|title=Player to Watch \u2013 John Guidetti|date=6 May 2010|accessdate=8 June 2010|work=imscouting.com|publisher=IMScouting}}</ref> [[F.C. Internazionale Milano|Inter Milan]], [[U.C. Sampdoria|Sampdoria]], [[S.S. Lazio|Lazio]], [[A.S. Roma|Roma]] and [[Ajax Cape Town F.C.|Ajax Cape Town]] ([[AFC Ajax|Ajax]]'s feeder club in South Africa), among others, had all been in competition for securing his services.<ref name=\"autogenerated1\">{{Cite news|url=http://www.dn.se/sport/fotboll/talangen-ar-redo-att-satsa-allt-1.794056|title=Talent is ready to do everything|language=Swedish|date=6 February 2009|accessdate=8 June 2010|work=dn.se|publisher=Dagens Nyheter|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100528103456/http://www.dn.se/sport/fotboll/talangen-ar-redo-att-satsa-allt-1.794056|archivedate=28 May 2010}}</ref>\n\n===Manchester City===\nManchester City's manager at the time, Sven Goran Eriksson, spotted Guidetti's talent in his native Sweden, and immediately signed him. Guidetti enjoyed a fine first season with the [[Manchester City F.C. Reserves and Academy|Manchester City]] under-18 team, scoring 13 times in 13 appearances. He also marked his reserve team debut with a remarkable [[hat-trick]] against a [[Burnley F.C.|Burnley]] side containing several seasoned campaigners.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.goal.com/en-india/news/222/transfer-zone/2010/05/27/1945376/roberto-mancini-set-to-hand-swedish-youngsterjohn-guidetti|title=Roberto Mancini set to hand Swedish youngster John Guidetti first-team chance at Manchester City \u2013 Report|date=27 May 2010|accessdate=8 June 2010|publisher=goal.com}}</ref>\n\n====Loan to IF Brommapojkarna====\nIn 2010, he went out on loan to his old club [[IF Brommapojkarna|Brommapojkarna]], impressing by scoring three goals and racking up three assists in only eight appearances.<ref name=\"Scout\" />\n\n====Return to Manchester City====\n[[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]]'s manager, [[Roberto Mancini]], wanted to see how the youngster matched up alongside the City first team, so he handed him a chance to impress on the club's pre-season tour in the United States during the summer of 2010.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://menmedia.co.uk/sport/football/manchester_city/s/1241230_city_set_to_launch_guidetti\n|title=City set to launch Guidetti|date=27 May 2010|accessdate=8 June 2010|work=menmedia.co.uk|publisher=Manchester Evening News}}</ref> During this American tour, Guidetti managed to make his debut for the Manchester City first team, coming on as a sub in the second half in a match against [[Sporting Clube de Portugal|Sporting Lisbon]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mcfc.co.uk/News/American-Pre-season-tour/2010/July/US-Tour-City-v-Sporting-match-report|title=US Tour: City slip to defeat|work=mcfc.co.uk|publisher=(Manchester City Football Club)|date=24 July 2010|accessdate=4 February 2011}}</ref>\nTwo months later back in England, Guidetti went on to make his full debut in a competitive match for the Manchester City first team when he was selected as striker for the starting lineup in the League Cup third round match against [[West Bromwich Albion F.C.|West Bromwich Albion]] on 22 September 2010, in which he provided the assist for City's only goal in the game.<ref>{{cite news\n|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/league_cup/9010120.stm|title=West Brom \u2013 Manchester City|date=22 September 2010|accessdate=22 September 2010|work=BBC Sport|publisher=British Broadcasting Corporation }}</ref>\n\n====Loan to Burnley====\nOn 25 November 2010, Guidetti signed an initial one-month loan deal with [[Burnley F.C.|Burnley]], with a possible option for Burnley to extend the loan when it expired on 1 January 2011.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport2/hi/football/teams/b/burnley/9228019.stm|title=Burnley sign Manchester City striker John Guidetti |date=25 November 2010|accessdate=4 February 2011|work=BBC Sport|publisher=British Broadcasting Corporation\n}}</ref> On 26 December 2010, in his first start for Burnley, he scored his first goal in a 2\u20131 victory at [[Barnsley F.C.|Barnsley]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/eng_div_1/9306376.stm|title=Barnsley 1 \u2013 2 Burnley|work=BBC Sport|publisher=British Broadcasting Corporation |date=26 December 2010|accessdate=29 December 2010}}</ref>\nManchester City would not extend his loan spell at Burnley, John was called back to parent club on 31 December 2010 to subsequently be added to Manchester City's registered 25-man squad for the [[2010\u201311 UEFA Europa League|Europa League]] competition.\n\n====Twente controversy====\nGuidetti's development contract with [[Manchester City F.C. Reserves and Academy|Manchester City]] was due to run out in July 2011. In late May, he visited [[Netherlands|Dutch]] club [[FC Twente|Twente]] with his father and several [[Sweden|Swedish]], [[Netherlands|Dutch]] and British media outlets reported he had signed a pre agreement with the Dutch club.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://fotboll.expressen.se/internationellt/1.2463022/nu-blir-guidetti-lag-kamrat-med-bajrami|title=Now Guidetti team-mate with Bajrami|language=Swedish|date=8 June 2011|accessdate=29 October 2011|work=Sportchef Expressen.se|publisher=AB Kv\u00e4llstidningen Expressen|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111008001246/http://fotboll.expressen.se/internationellt/1.2463022/nu-blir-guidetti-lag-kamrat-med-bajrami|archive-date=8 October 2011|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.fotbollskanalen.se/1.2151882/2011/05/25/guidetti_gar_till_twente_skrivit_pa_fyraarskontrakt|title=Guidetti goes to Twente \u2013 written on four-year contract|language=Swedish|date=25 May 2011|accessdate=29 October 2011|work=Fotbollskanalen.se|publisher=TV4 AB\n}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.fotbollskanalen.se/1.2158774/2011/05/30/bajrami_tipsade_twente_om_guidetti|title=Bajrami tipped Twente on Guidetti |language=Swedish|date=30 May 2011|accessdate=29 October 2011|work=Fotbollskanalen.se|publisher=TV4 AB\n}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.skysports.com/story/0,19528,11906_6952861,00.html|title=City striker set for Twente|date=26 May 2011|accessdate=29 October 2011|work=www.skysports.com|publisher=skySPORTS\n}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.setanta.com/ien/Articles/2011/05/26/City-teen-set-to-go-Dutch/gnid-95537/|title=Guidetti to leave City|date=26 May 2011|accessdate=29 October 2011|work=setanta.com|publisher=Setanta Sports|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110612120033/http://www.setanta.com/ien/Articles/2011/05/26/City-teen-set-to-go-Dutch/gnid-95537/|archivedate=12 June 2011}}</ref> In mid June, reports indicated that there were problems with this agreement. Twente understood they had a [[Bosman ruling|Bosman deal]] agreed with Guidetti's camp, but agent Per Jonsson insisted nothing had been agreed upon in contract. Twente chairman Joop Munsterman said: \"We do not know if Mr. Jonsson is his agent. We have done business with Mike [Guidetti] (the father of the player). The most important thing for a young player like Guidetti is that he plays a lot of games. For that reason, Twente is the logical choice.\" <ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.fcupdate.nl/voetbalnieuws/178291/komst-guidetti-naar-twente-op-losse-schroeven/|title=Guidetti coming to Twente for loose screws|language=Dutch|date=14 June 2011|accessdate=29 October 2011|work=fcupdate.nl|publisher=JHED Media Ltd}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.telegraaf.nl/telesport/voetbal/fctwente/10017825/__Problemen_rond_transfer_Guidetti__.html|title=Problems surrounding Guidetti transfer|language=Dutch|date=14 June 2011|accessdate=29 October 2011|work=telegraaf.nl|publisher=Telegraaf Media Nederland|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120301234852/http://www.telegraaf.nl/telesport/voetbal/fctwente/10017825/__Problemen_rond_transfer_Guidetti__.html|archive-date=1 March 2012|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.eurosport.se/fotboll/twente-kritiserar-agenten_sto2837729/story.shtml|title=Twente criticize the agent: \"Guidetti is ready\"|language=Swedish|date=17 June 2011|accessdate=29 October 2011|work=eurosport.se|publisher=EUROSPORT}}</ref>\n\nThe [[Netherlands|Dutch]] football association ''FBO'' (Federatie Betaald Voetbal Organization), let a [[lawyer]] review the preliminary agreement between John Guidetti and Twente. The club announced that the contract should be regarded as valid. \u2013 \"In our opinion it is a valid contract. We look forward to welcoming John for his first practice 1 July\", said Twente chairman Joop Munsterman to ''[[Voetbal International]]'' magazine.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.telegraaf.nl/telesport/voetbal/fctwente/10086135/___Guidetti_op_1_juli_bij_FC_Twente___.html|title=Guidetti at FC Twente on July 1|language=Dutch|date=24 June 2011|accessdate=29 October 2011|work=telegraaf.nl|publisher=Telegraaf Media Nederland|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110829101429/http://www.telegraaf.nl/telesport/voetbal/fctwente/10086135/___Guidetti_op_1_juli_bij_FC_Twente___.html|archive-date=29 August 2011|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.fotbollskanalen.se/1.2186791/2011/06/24/hollandska_forbundet_kontraktet_med_guidetti_galler |title=Dutch League \u2013 \"contract with Guidetti case\"|language=Swedish|date=24 June 2011|accessdate=29 October 2011|work=Fotbollskanalen.se|publisher=TV4 AB}}</ref>\n\nOn 9 July 2011, Manchester City released a set of photographs as the team set off on a North American pre-season tour. Despite his alleged transfer to Twente, Guidetti was spotted in the photos taken at the airport with his Manchester City teammates.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.flickr.com/photos/mcfcofficial/5917104135/in/set72157627026030355/#/photos/mcfcofficial/5917104135/in/set-72157627026030355/lightbox/|title=Summer tour: Travelling |date=9 July 2011|accessdate=29 October 2011|work=Flickr.com|publisher=(Yahoo Inc.)\n}}</ref> On 19 July 2011, Guidetti was offered and signed a first team contract binding him to the club of Manchester City for three more years.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.skysports.com/story/0,19528,12875_7046760,00.html|title=Guidetti commits to City|date=18 July 2011|accessdate=29 October 2011|work=skysports.com|publisher=skySPORTS}}</ref>\n\n====Loan to Feyenoord====\n[[File:Jeroen-zoet-keeper-rkc-waalwijk-1324915570.jpg|thumb|right|Guidetti (right) playing for [[Feyenoord]] in 2011, challenging [[RKC Waalwijk]] goalkeeper [[Jeroen Zoet]]]]\nOn the last day of the transfer window, [[Feyenoord]] and Manchester City agreed a loan deal for the rest of the 2011\u201312 season.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.mcfc.co.uk/news/team-news/2011/august/john-guidetti-loaned-to-feyenoord|title=Guidetti loaned to Feyenoord|publisher=Manchester City FC|date=31 August 2011|accessdate=21 June 2012}}</ref> Guidetti made his debut in the game against [[NAC Breda]] on 11 September 2011 in which he scored a penalty.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.sportqa.com/Feyenoord-Rotterdams-John-Guidetti-delighted-to-score-against-NAC-Breda-Dutch-Eredivisie-news-a29713|title=Feyenoord Rotterdam's John Guidetti delighted to score against NAC Breda \u2013 Dutch Eredivisie news|publisher=SportQA|date=11 September 2011|accessdate=21 June 2012}}</ref> He also scored a penalty in the match against [[De Graafschap]] and 2 more from the penalty spot against [[VVV-Venlo]]. He scored his first goal from open play for Feyenoord against [[Vitesse Arnhem|Vitesse]] in the 4\u20130 away win, netting two goals in the game.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.footreview.net/home/viewvideo/933/eredivisie-netherlands/vitesse-0-4-feyenoord-highlights|title=Vitesse 0 \u2013 4 Feyenoord Highlights|publisher=Foot Review|date=20 November 2011|accessdate=21 June 2012}}</ref> The following week he scored another crucial goal, the equaliser in a 2\u20131 away win against [[RKC Waalwijk]]. On 18 December 2011 he scored a [[hat-trick]] in Feyenoord's 3\u20132 victory against [[FC Twente]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.caughtoffside.com/2011/12/18/man-city-striker-john-guidetti-scores-hat-trick-for-feyenoord-against-fc-twente/|title=Man City Striker John Guidetti Scores Hat-Trick for Feyenoord Against FC Twente|publisher=Cuaght Offside|date=18 December 2011|accessdate=21 June 2012}}</ref>\n\nOn 29 January 2012, he scored his second consecutive hat-trick, scoring three goals in [[De Klassieker]] against [[AFC Ajax|Ajax]], which Feyenoord won 4\u20132, their first victory in 6 years over the arch-rivals.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://uk.eurosport.yahoo.com/29012012/2/guidetti-hat-trick-feyenoord-sinks-ajax.html|title=Guidetti hat-trick for Feyenoord sinks Ajax|publisher=Yahoo! Eurosport/Reuters|date=29 January 2012|accessdate=21 June 2012}}</ref> This helped earning him a hero status in Rotterdam, with coach Ronald Koeman describing him as \"phenomenal\".<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.voetbalprimeur.nl/nieuws/item/koeman-ziet-angst-guidetti-een-fenomeen|title=Koeman ziet angst: \"Guidetti een fenomeen\"|publisher=Voetbalprimeur|language=Dutch|date=30 January 2012|accessdate=21 June 2012|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140116101427/http://www.voetbalprimeur.nl/nieuws/item/koeman-ziet-angst-guidetti-een-fenomeen|archivedate=16 January 2014}}</ref> On 12 February he scored his third hat-trick since joining the club in a home game in a 3\u20131 win against Vitesse, putting him third in Europe for goals scored/minutes played, at 17 goals after 15 league appearances.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://thepremierleagueowl.com/man-citys-john-guidetti-hitting-another-hat-trick-in-holland/|title=Man City's John Guidetti hitting another hat-trick in Holland|publisher=The Premier League Owl|date=12 February 2012|accessdate=21 June 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140116124843/http://thepremierleagueowl.com/man-citys-john-guidetti-hitting-another-hat-trick-in-holland/|archive-date=16 January 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref> This happened to be the third consecutive hat-trick in an [[Eredivisie]] home game, becoming the second player in the history of the league to achieve this after [[Cees Groot]] did this in 1963.<ref name=\"groot\">{{cite news|url=http://www.telegraaf.nl/telesport/voetbal/feyenoord/11501089/__Guidetti_evenaart_Groot__.html|title=Guidetti evenaart Groot|publisher=De Telegraaf|language=Dutch|date=12 February 2012|accessdate=21 June 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120318123259/http://www.telegraaf.nl/telesport/voetbal/feyenoord/11501089/__Guidetti_evenaart_Groot__.html|archive-date=18 March 2012|url-status=dead}}</ref> [[Ove Kindvall]] was the last Swede to achieve this in the Dutch league in the 1970s, also playing for Feyenoord.<ref name=\"groot\"/> Also, Guidetti was the first Feyenoord player to score three hat-tricks in one season since [[Dirk Kuyt]] in 2004\u201305.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.ad.nl/ad/nl/5610/Eredivisie/article/detail/3174628/2012/02/12/LIVE-Guidetti-scoort-meteen-na-opvallende-balwissel.dhtml|title=Guidetti zet Kuip met hattrick weer in vuur en vlam|language=Dutch|publisher=Algemeen Dagblad|date=12 February 2012|accessdate=21 June 2012}}</ref>\n\nGuidetti scored his 18th goal from the penalty spot in his 16th league game against [[RKC Waalwijk]], and celebrated by pulling his shirt off which gave him his second yellow card in the game.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2103224/Manchester-City-John-Guidetti-costly-goal-celebration.html|title=Guid to bad! City hot shot feels wrath of boss after costly goal celebration|publisher=Daily Mail|date=18 February 2012|accessdate=21 June 2012}}</ref> The opponents then equalized three minutes before the end, and Guidetti later apologized to the team, the supporters and the coach, saying it was \"one of the worst moments in my life\".<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www1.skysports.com/football/news/11916/7535629/Guidetti-says-sorry-for-red-card|title=Guidetti says sorry for red card|publisher=Sky Sports|date=21 February 2012|accessdate=21 June 2012}}</ref> Due to this red card, Guidetti missed the important game in the title challenge against [[PSV Eindhoven]] the following week. A couple of weeks later, Guidetti scored his next goal away to [[De Graafschap]] in a 3\u20130 win.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.mcfc.co.uk/news/team-news/2012/march/loan-watch-27-march-john-guidetti-back-in-form|title=Loan watch:Guidetti back in the groove|publisher=Manchester City FC|date=27 March 2012|accessdate=21 June 2012}}</ref> He scored his 20th, and final, goal of the season in a 3\u20130 city-derby home win over [[Excelsior Rotterdam]] in April. Guidetti then missed the rest of the Eredivisie season, as well as [[UEFA Euro 2012]], after losing all feeling in his right leg while suffering from a mystery virus.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/sport/football/news/manchester-city-john-guidetti-struck-810742|title=Mystery virus: City striker loses all feeling in his leg|publisher=The Mirror|date=28 April 2012|accessdate=21 June 2012}}</ref>\n\nWithout the injured Guidetti, Feyenoord managed to secure only second spot of the league, but it guaranteed them a place in the qualification rounds for the [[2012\u201313 UEFA Champions League]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.foxnews.com/sports/2012/05/06/feyenoord-claims-champions-league-spot-in-eredivisie/|title=Feyenoord claims Champions League spot in Eredivisie|publisher=Fox News|date=6 May 2012|accessdate=21 June 2012}}</ref> Guidetti, who watched from home the game against [[SC Heerenveen]] which clinched second place, was then carried on the shoulders of some Feyenoord fans towards [[De Kuip]] stadium to celebrate this achievement.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://feyenoord.netwerk.to/nieuws/artikel/26521_%5BFoto%5D%20Guidetti%20op%20de%20schouders.php|title=Guidetti op de schouders|publisher=Feyenoord Network|language=Dutch|date=6 May 2012|accessdate=21 June 2012}}</ref> Later on he was seen singing \"Feyenoord till I die\" with the fans at the stadium and singing a Champions League song at the pitch amongst the other players.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.fr12.nl/dump/8130-guidetti--i--m-feyenoord-till-i-die-.html|title=Guidetti, I'm Feyenoord till I die.|publisher=FR 12|date=10 May 2012|accessdate=21 June 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.fr12.nl/dump/8074-guidetti-zet-de-kuip-op-zijn-kop.html|title=Guidetti zet de Kuip op zijn kop|publisher=FR 12|language=Dutch|date=6 May 2012|accessdate=21 June 2012}}</ref> In total, Guidetti scored 20 goals and provided eight assists in 23 games for Feyenoord during this loan spell.\n\n====Struggling for fitness====\nGuidetti was back at Man City for the start of 2012\u201313, but spent the most of the season struggling to recover from the virus that curtailed his spell at Feyenoord. The severity of the disorder saw Guidetti diagnosed with an infected nerve, which caused him to lose feeling in his right leg.<ref name=\"ill\">{{cite web|last1=Beresford|first1=Jack|title=Whatever happened to Manchester City's John Guidetti?|url=http://www.ftbpro.com/posts/99607-whatever-happened-to-manchester-city-s-john-guidetti|publisher=FTB Pro|accessdate=4 November 2014|date=5 January 2013}}</ref>  Commenting about Guidetti's condition, assistant manager [[David Platt (footballer)|David Platt]] explained, \"For about two or three months he [Guidetti] couldn't do anything and it takes a long time to get that back.\"<ref name=\"ill\" />  Despite this, Guidetti signed a new three-year deal with Manchester City on 18 October 2012, keeping him at the Etihad Stadium until 2015.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/19991206 |title=Manchester City Striker John Guidetti signs new contract |date=18 October 2012 |accessdate=18 October 2012 |publisher=BBC Sport}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.footballfriendsonline.com/blogs/2012/10/18/outrageous-guidetti-shows-why-man-city-have-given-him-new-3.html|title=Outrageous Guidetti shows why Man City have given him new 4 year contract|date=18 October 2012|accessdate=18 October 2012|publisher=Footballfriends.com|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121022113017/http://www.footballfriendsonline.com/blogs/2012/10/18/outrageous-guidetti-shows-why-man-city-have-given-him-new-3.html|archivedate=22 October 2012}}</ref>\n\nHe finally returned to playing football on 14 January 2013 when he played in the first half of an [[2012\u201313 Professional U21 Development League|Under 21 League]] match between City and [[Reading F.C. Under-21s and Academy|Reading U21s]], scoring the opening goal in a 3\u20131 win.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Brennan|first1=Stuart|title=John Guidetti joy at Blues return|url=http://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/john-guidetti-joy-at-blues-return-1210318|publisher=Manchester Evening News|accessdate=4 November 2014|date=15 January 2013}}</ref>  Guidetti scored a further five goals in his next six games for the Development Side,<ref name=\"knee\">{{cite web|last1=Dawson|first1=Rob|title=Fresh-faced Blues get a fresh start|url=http://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/fresh-faced-blues-fresh-start-3869404|publisher=Manchester Evening News|accessdate=4 November 2014|date=18 May 2013}}</ref> before sucummbing to a knee injury which later required surgery.<ref name=\"knee\" /><ref>{{cite web|last1=Dawson|first1=Rob|title=Pellegrini praise for Guidetti recovery|url=http://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/manuel-pellegrini-praise-john-guidetti-6207834|publisher=Manchester Evening News|accessdate=4 November 2014|date=18 October 2013}}</ref>\n\n====Loan to Stoke City====\nOn 14 January 2014, Guidetti joined [[Stoke City F.C.|Stoke City]] on loan for the remainder of the [[2013\u201314 Stoke City F.C. season|2013\u201314]] season.<ref>{{cite web|title=Guidetti Joins On Loan|url=http://www.stokecityfc.com/news/article/guidetti-joins-on-loan-1294155.aspx|work=Stoke City F.C|accessdate=14 January 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Transfer window: Stephen Ireland & John Guidetti join Stoke City|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/25720354|work=BBC Sport|accessdate=15 January 2014}}</ref> He made his debut on 18 January 2014 coming on as a substitute in a 1\u20130 defeat against [[Crystal Palace F.C.|Crystal Palace]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Crystal Palace 1\u20130 Stoke|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/25693671|work=BBC Sport|accessdate=19 January 2014}}</ref> After not playing in Stoke's next match against [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]] in the [[FA Cup]], Guidetti vented his frustration towards manager [[Mark Hughes]] to the Swedish media.<ref>{{cite web|title=John Guidetti annoyed to spend another week on the bench after Chelsea defeat|url=http://www.stokesentinel.co.uk/Stoke-City-John-Guidetti-annoyed-spend-week-bench/story-20503993-detail/story.html|work=Stoke Sentinel|accessdate=30 March 2014}}</ref> Guidetti later insisted that he was not being disrespectful to Hughes.<ref>{{cite web|title=John Guidetti denies disrespecting Mark Hughes|url=http://www.stokesentinel.co.uk/Stoke-City-John-Guidetti-denies-disrespecting/story-20806645-detail/story.html|work=Stoke Sentinel|accessdate=30 March 2014}}</ref> He had an unsuccessful time at Stoke as he made just six appearances, all of them as a substitute.<ref>{{Soccerbase season|56208|2013|name=John Guidetti|access-date=12 May 2014}}</ref>\n\n====Loan to Celtic====\nOn 4 September 2014, Guidetti joined [[Scottish Premiership]] side [[Celtic F.C.|Celtic]] on loan for the [[2014\u201315 Celtic F.C. season|2014\u201315]] season,<ref>{{cite web|title=John Guidetti joins Celtic|url=http://www.celticfc.net/news/6578|website=Celtic|accessdate=4 September 2014}}</ref> but was ineligible for the [[UEFA Europe League]] group stages.<ref>[https://archive.today/20140905142927/http://m.stv.tv/sport/football/clubs/celtic/290993-celtics-europa-league-squad-confirmed-john-guidetti-not-included/ Celtic's Europa League squad confirmed] STV. 5 September 2014. Retrieved 22 February 2015.</ref> He made his debut nine days later, replacing [[Scott Brown (footballer, born June 1985)|Scott Brown]] for the final 29 minutes of a 2\u20131 home win over [[Aberdeen F.C.|Aberdeen]].<ref>{{cite news|last1=Southwick|first1=Andrew|title=Celtic 2\u20131 Aberdeen|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/29090522|accessdate=13 September 2014|work=[[BBC Sport]]|date=13 September 2014}}</ref> On 24 September he scored his first Celtic goal, opening a 3\u20130 home win over [[Heart of Midlothian F.C.|Heart of Midlothian]] in the last 16 of the [[Scottish League Cup]].<ref>{{cite news|last=Moffat|first=Colin|title=Celtic 3\u20130 Hearts|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/29233038|accessdate=25 September 2014|work=BBC Sport|date=24 September 2014}}</ref> Three days later he scored his first Premiership goals, netting both as Celtic won 2\u20131 at [[St Mirren F.C.|St Mirren]].<ref>{{cite news|last1=Campbell|first1=Andy|title=St Mirren 1\u20132 Celtic|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/29289908|accessdate=27 September 2014|work=BBC Sport|date=27 September 2014}}</ref>\n\nHe scored a hat-trick on 29 October, as Celtic advanced to the semi-finals of the [[Scottish League Cup]] with a 6\u20130 win over [[Partick Thistle F.C.|Partick Thistle]].<ref>{{cite news|last1=Mcleod|first1=Liam|title=Celtic 6\u20130 Partick Thistle|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/29718349|accessdate=30 October 2014|work=BBC Sport|date=29 October 2014}}</ref> His treble was the 15th hat-trick scored at Celtic by a Swedish player.<ref>[https://twitter.com/splstats/status/527565231493742592 SPL Stats on Twitter] Twitter. 29 October 2014. Retrieved 9 May 2015.</ref> Three days later he scored the only goal in a league win over [[Inverness Caledonian Thistle F.C.|Inverness Caledonian Thistle]], his ninth goal in his last seven games.<ref>{{cite news|last=Wilson|first=Richard|title=Celtic 1\u20130 Inverness|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/29767941|accessdate=1 November 2014|work=BBC Sport|date=1 November 2014}}</ref> He was named as the Premiership Player of the Month for October 2014, with six goals in four games, all won by Celtic.<ref name=\"pom1014\">{{cite news|title=Celtic: striker John Guidetti lands October SPFL player award|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/29932441|accessdate=17 November 2014|work=BBC Sport|date=6 November 2014}}</ref>\n\nGuidetti scored a penalty in Celtic's 4\u20130 win at [[Heart of Midlothian F.C.|Heart of Midlothian]] in the fourth round of the [[Scottish Cup]] on 30 November; its awarding was controversial as the Hearts players protested that he had dived under pressure from [[Brad McKay]].<ref>{{cite news|last1=Southwick|first1=Andrew|title=Hearts 0\u20134 Celtic|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/30166217|accessdate=30 November 2014|work=BBC Sport|date=30 November 2014}}</ref> It was his 11th goal in just 10 games for Celtic,<ref name=11in10>[http://www1.skysports.com/football/news/12040/9711791/spfl-celtic-manager-ronny-deila-backing-john-guidetti-to-start-scoring-again SPFL: Celtic manager Ronny Deila backing John Guidetti to start scoring again] Sky Sports. 14 February 2015. Retrieved 22 February 2015.</ref> after which Guidetti embarked on run of  10 games without a goal,<ref>[http://www.dailyrecord.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/inter-milan-boss-roberto-mancini-5166387 Inter Milan boss Roberto Mancini fears] Daily Record. 15 February 2015. Retrieved 22 January 2015.</ref> and lost his place in the starting eleven to [[Leigh Griffiths]].<ref name=11in10/> However, on as a second-half substitute in the [[UEFA Europa League]] match against [[Internazionale|Inter Milan]] on 19 February, he rescued a 3\u20133 draw for Celtic with a stoppage-time equaliser,<ref name=3v3InterMilan>[http://www.dailyrecord.co.uk/sport/football/football-match-reports/celtic-3-inter-milan-3-5195871 Celtic 3: Inter 3] Daily Record. 20 February 2015. Retrieved 22 February 2015.</ref> controlling a lobbed pass onto his chest before volleying into the roof of the net.<ref name=3v3InterMilan/>\n\nOn 15 March, Guidetti won his first silverware at Celtic, as they defeated [[Dundee United F.C.|Dundee United]] 2\u20130 in the [[2015 Scottish League Cup Final|League Cup Final]] at [[Hampden Park]]. He came on in the 69th minute for Griffiths, and 15 minutes later when [[James Forrest (footballer)|James Forrest]] won a penalty, Celtic players wanted Guidetti to take it; Forrest took it himself and it was saved by [[Rados\u0142aw Cierzniak]].<ref name=bbcfinal>{{cite news|title=Dundee Utd 0\u20132 Celtic|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/31785677|accessdate=15 March 2015|work=BBC Sport|date=14 March 2015|first=Richard|last=Wilson}}</ref> Prior to that, Guidetti had assisted Forest for Celtic's second goal.<ref>[http://www.scotsman.com/sport/football/latest/celtic-2-0-dundee-united-hoops-win-league-cup-1-3719080 Celtic 2\u20130 Dundee United] The Scotsman. 16 March 2015. Retrieved 23 February 2015.</ref> On 19 April, in a Scottish Cup semi-final at Hampden Park, he came on for Griffiths in extra time and equalised against Inverness, although Celtic eventually lost 2\u20133.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Lindsay|first1=Clive|title=Inverness CT 3\u20132 Celtic|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/32089585|accessdate=19 April 2015|work=BBC Sport|date=19 April 2015}}</ref> It was his 15th goal of the season.<ref>[http://hereisthecity.com/en-gb/2015/05/02/report-celtic-loanee-john-guidetti-is-ignoring-calls-from-feyeno/ Report: Celtic loanee John Guidetti is ignoring calls from Feyenoord over his signature] HITC. May 2015. Retrieved 9 May 2015.</ref> Guidetti finished the season with 15 goals from 35 appearances for Celtic.<ref>[http://www.soccerbase.com/players/player.sd?player_id=56208&season_id=144 John Guidetti career stats 2014\u201315] Soccer Base. Retrieved 29 May 2015.</ref>\n\nAt the end of the 2014\u201315 season, it was announced that parent club Manchester City did not intend to offer Guidetti a new contract, and would become a free agent once his contract expired along with teammate [[Micah Richards]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sportinglife.com/football/transfer-centre/article/168/9880981/john-guidetti-released |title=Lampard among released players |date=10 June 2015 |publisher=SportingLife |accessdate=11 June 2015}}</ref>\n\n===Celta===\nOn 11 July 2015, Guidetti signed for [[La Liga]] club [[Celta de Vigo]] on a [[free transfer (association football)|free transfer]], after agreeing to a five-year contract.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/33493812 |title=John Guidetti: Celta Vigo sign ex-Manchester City striker |publisher=BBC Sport |date=11 July 2015 |accessdate=11 July 2015}}</ref> He made his debut on 23 August as a 69th-minute substitute for [[Hugo Mallo]] in a 2\u20131 win at [[Levante UD|Levante]], and scored his first goal on 23 September, a volley to confirm a 4\u20131 win over reigning champions [[FC Barcelona]] five minutes after entering as a replacement for [[Iago Aspas]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Iago Aspas scores twice as Celta Vigo give Barcelona shock thrashing|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2015/sep/23/celta-vigo-barcelona-match-report|accessdate=24 September 2015|agency=Reuters|publisher=The Guardian|date=23 September 2015}}</ref> On 27 January 2016, Guidetti scored with a 25-metre volley in a 3\u20132 win over [[Atl\u00e9tico Madrid]] in the quarter-finals of the [[Copa del Rey]], helping his side reach the semi-finals of the Cup for the first time in 15 years.<ref>{{cite news|title=Celta Vigo shock Atl\u00e9tico Madrid to progress to Copa del Rey last four|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2016/jan/27/atletico-madrid-celta-vigo-copa-del-rey-quarter-final|accessdate=1 April 2016|work=The Guardian|date=27 January 2016}}</ref>\n\n===Alav\u00e9s===\nOn 8 January 2018, Guidetti was loaned to fellow first division club [[Deportivo Alav\u00e9s]], until the end of [[2017\u201318 La Liga|the season]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.deportivoalaves.com/noticia/el-deportivo-alaves-incorpora-a-john-guidetti|title=El Deportivo Alav\u00e9s incorpora a John Guidetti|trans-title=Deportivo Alav\u00e9s sign John Guidetti|publisher=Deportivo Alav\u00e9s|language=es|date=8 January 2018|access-date=29 May 2018}}</ref> On 29 May, he signed a permanent four-year deal with the club.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://as.com/futbol/2018/05/29/primera/1527587645_008095.html|title=Guidetti, del Alav\u00e9s hasta 2022|trans-title=Guidetti, of Alav\u00e9s until 2022|publisher=[[Diario AS]]|language=es|date=29 May 2018|access-date=29 May 2018}}</ref>\n\nOn 17 January 2020, Guidetti was loaned out to [[Hannover 96]] for the rest of the 2019\u201320 season.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hannover96.de/aktuelles/news/details/26717-schwedischer-nationalstuermer-fuer-96-john-guidetti-kommt-aus-alaves.html|title=Schwedischer Nationalst\u00fcrmer f\u00fcr 96: Guidetti kommt aus Alav\u00e9s|publisher=Hannover 96|lang=German|date=17 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n==International career==\n[[File:Oscar Hiljemark and John Guidetti in June 2015.jpg|thumb|right|Guidetti celebrating the [[2015 UEFA European Under-21 Championship|2015 European Under-21 Championship]]]]\n\n===Youth===\nGuidetti played 14 matches and scored 14 goals for Sweden's Under-19 national squads, including four goals against the Netherlands. Although initially considered to be beyond selection to play for the [[Sweden national under-21 football team|Sweden U21]] team (who were leading their European Championship qualifying group at the time) in the June 2010 fixtures against [[Israel national under-21 football team|Israel]] and [[Montenegro national under-21 football team|Montenegro]], Guidetti ultimately got his chance to play at this higher level as a replacement for the injured first choice striker [[Agon Mehmeti]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.aftonbladet.se/sportbladet/fotboll/landslagsfotboll/u21/article7211753.ab|title=Hallenius and Guidetti called in to the European Championship qualifiers|language=Swedish|date=29 May 2010|accessdate=8 June 2010|work=aftonbladet.se|publisher=SPORT Bladet}}</ref>\nGuidetti accordingly took his place in the Sweden U21 team's starting eleven that manage to win away 1\u20130 against [[Israel national under-21 football team|Israel]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.dn.se/sport/fotboll/sveriges-u21-herrar-slog-israel-1.1116961|title=Sweden's under-21 men beat Israel|language=Swedish|date=4 June 2010|accessdate=8 June 2010|work=dn.se|publisher=Dagens Nyheter|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100607033121/http://www.dn.se/sport/fotboll/sveriges-u21-herrar-slog-israel-1.1116961|archivedate=7 June 2010}}</ref>\n\nGuidetti earnt his next international cap when he was included in the [[Sweden national youth football team|Sweden U19]] team rather than the Sweden U21 team because according to Swedish Under-21 national team coach, [[J\u00f6rgen Lennartsson]], they had even \"greater need\" for him back in the younger team.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.fotbollskanalen.se/1.1733847/2010/08/03/har_ar_lennartssons_trupp_till_u21_landslaget_ingen_guidetti_med|title=Here is Lenny's squad for the Under-21 squad \u2013 no Guidetti|language=Swedish|date=3 August 2010|accessdate=10 September 2010|work=Fotbollskanalen.se|publisher=TV4 AB\n}}</ref> He scored after just four minutes in his first game back with the Under-19 line-up against [[Poland national under-19 football team|Poland]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.expressen.se/sport/sanktan/stockholm/1.2092732/p92-saker-3-1-seger-mot-polen |title=P92: Secure 3\u20131 win against Poland |language=Swedish|date=11 August 2010|accessdate=11 August 2010|work=Expressen.se|publisher=AB Kv\u00e4llstidningen Expressen}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://sport.onet.pl/pilka-nozna/reprezentacja/mlodzi-polacy-nie-sprostali-szwedom,1,3416526,wiadomosc.html|title=Young Poles are no match for the Swedes|language=Polish|date=10 August 2010|accessdate=10 August 2010|work=Sport.onet.pl|publisher=Grupa Onet.pl SA|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110617111648/http://sport.onet.pl/pilka-nozna/reprezentacja/mlodzi-polacy-nie-sprostali-szwedom,1,3416526,wiadomosc.html|archivedate=17 June 2011}}</ref> After the Sweden U21 team suffered a surprise home defeat against Israel without Guidetti, John was recalled once again to play for this team in its decisive qualifying match against [[Bulgaria national under-19 football team|Bulgaria]], where he created the winning and only goal for Sweden in a 1\u20130 victory.\n\nAt the [[2015 UEFA European Under-21 Championship|2015 European Under-21 Championship]] in the Czech Republic, Guidetti equalised as Sweden came from behind to defeat [[Italy national under-21 football team|Italy]] 2\u20131 in their opening group game in [[Olomouc]].<ref>{{cite news|title=U21 round-up: Sweden stun Italy|url=http://www1.skysports.com/football/news/11095/9889364/u21-round-up-sweden-stun-italy|accessdate=21 June 2015|publisher=Sky Sports|date=18 June 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/33063307|title=England U21 0\u20131 Portugal U21|publisher=BBC Sport|last1=Jurejko|first1=Jonathan|date=18 June 2015|accessdate=30 June 2015}}</ref> He took and scored Sweden's first spot-kick in the [[Penalty shoot-out (association football)|penalty shootout]] in [[2015 UEFA European Under-21 Championship Final|the final]] against [[Portugal national under-21 football team|Portugal]], which his team won after a 0\u20130 draw in [[Prague]].<ref name=\"uefa21\">{{cite news|url=http://www.uefa.com/under21/season=2015/matches/round=2000411/match=2015383/postmatch/report/index.html|title=Sweden beat Portugal on penalties to win U21 title|publisher=UEFA.com|date=30 June 2015|accessdate=30 June 2015}}</ref>\n\n===Senior===\nGuidetti debuted with the [[Sweden national football team|Sweden]] senior squad on 29 February 2012 in a friendly away to [[Croatia national football team|Croatia]], coming on as a half-time substitute.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.dn.se/sport/fotboll/godkant-debut-av-guidetti|title=Zlatan wants Guidetti in Euro 2012|language=Swedish|date=29 February 2012|accessdate=29 February 2012|work=dn.se|publisher=Dagens Nyheter|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120229234641/http://www.dn.se/sport/fotboll/godkant-debut-av-guidetti|archivedate=29 February 2012}}</ref> He had to wait over two-and-a-half years for his second cap, replacing [[Isaac Thelin]] for the last 23 minutes of a 1\u20130 friendly defeat to [[France national football team|France]] in [[Marseille]] on 18 November 2014.<ref>{{cite news|title=France 1\u20130 Sweden: Varane secures win for dominant Bleus|url=http://www.goal.com/en/match/france-vs-sweden/1946143/report|accessdate=19 November 2014|work=Goal.com|date=18 November 2014}}</ref> He scored his first goal for Sweden on 5 June 2016, netting the third in a 3\u20130 friendly win over [[Wales national football team|Wales]].<ref name=1st>{{cite news|last=Davies|first=Jack (5 June 2016)|url=http://www.goal.com/en-za/match/sweden-vs-wales/2206332/report|title=Sweden 3\u20130 Wales: Coleman's men winless in four ahead of Euros|accessdate=5 June 2016|website=Goal}}</ref>\n\nHe was a squad player for Sweden at [[Euro 2016]].<ref name=\"goal.com\"/>\n\nIn May 2018 he was named in [[Sweden national football team|Sweden's]] [[Sweden national football team|23 man squad]] for the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]] in Russia.<ref>http://www.goal.com/en-gb/amp/news/revealed-every-world-cup-2018-squad-23-man-preliminary-lists/oa0atsduflsv1nsf6oqk576rb</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nGuidetti's paternal grandfather is [[Italy|Italian]] and his paternal grandmother is half [[Swedes|Swedish]], half [[Brazil]]ian.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.svtplay.se/video/323068/del-4-av-12 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=3 October 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121002202648/http://www.svtplay.se/video/323068/del-4-av-12 |archivedate= 2 October 2012 }}</ref> Guidetti has lived in [[Kenya]] on two occasions with his father Mike, mother Susanne and his sister Carmen. Guidetti credits playing football with older children from the poorer slum areas of [[Kibera]] and [[Mathare]] as an important step in his development on and off the field, and founded a NGO that helps children in the area.<ref>http://www.guidettifoundation.org/</ref>\n\nIn the summer of 2015, Swedish music group Badpojken made a song about Guidetti, called \"Johnny G (The Guidetti Song)\".<ref>{{cite news|title=Ystadsgrupp har gjort hyllingsl\u00e5t till John Guidetti|url=http://www.ystadsallehanda.se/sport/ystadsgrupp-har-gjort-hyllingslat-till-john-guidetti/|accessdate=13 November 2017|work=Ystads Allehanda|date=7 July 2015}}</ref> It peaked [[List of number-one singles and albums in Sweden|number 1]] at the [[Sverigetopplistan|Swedish music charts]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Badpojken \u2013 Johnny G (The Guidetti Song)|url=http://www.ultratop.be/nl/song/1642f1/Badpojken-Johnny-G-(The-Guidetti-Song)|accessdate=13 November 2017|work=Ultratop}}</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n===Club===\n{{updated|match played on 18 May 2019}}<ref>{{cite web\n|url=http://soccernet.espn.go.com/players/profile?id=136381&league=ENG.1&season=2009&cc=5739|title= Statistics|publisher=ESPN Soccernet|accessdate=22 September 2009 }}</ref><ref>[https://svenskfotboll.se/allsvenskan/person/?playerid=5856 John Guidetti \u2014 svenskfotboll.se]</ref><ref name=\"sway\">{{cite web|title= J. GUIDETTI|url=https://int.soccerway.com/players/john-guidetti/126941/|publisher=Soccerway.com|accessdate=15 June 2016}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Club\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Season\n!colspan